{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"54b09b94-7edd-49b1-8927-9e73bb26f330","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as \"skipped\" (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3d1c6130-9ac7-49c8-b095-2540e3fe60d9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute/annotation to use for skipping tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide this from my knowledge.","outputTokens":332,"requestId":"BD0D:319933:1CA1E82:204986C:6A07C4EC"},"id":"80c1c099-40ca-49a4-9f90-6f8cfc5c64c8","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:14:26.802Z","parentId":"8017bdd1-cb39-4d1d-96b5-d0b5cbd1153c"}
